---
import BooruLegalLayout from "../../layouts/BooruLegalLayout.astro";

const updated = "May 31, 2026";
const githubUrl = "https://github.com/watzon/booru-browser";
---

<BooruLegalLayout
  title="Booru Browser — Terms of Use"
  description="The terms that govern your use of Booru Browser: a free, open-source client that connects only to the booru servers you choose to add."
  heading="Terms of Use"
  updated={updated}
>
  <p>
    Booru Browser is a free, open-source client application developed by Chris
    Watson (“I”, “me”). By installing or using the app, you agree to these terms.
    If you do not agree, please do not use the app.
  </p>

  <h2>The app</h2>
  <p>
    Booru Browser is provided free of charge as open-source software. The source
    code is available on <a href={githubUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
    and your use of that code is governed by the license published there. These
    terms cover your use of the application itself, not the third-party content it
    can display.
  </p>

  <h2>No accounts, no servers</h2>
  <p>
    The app has no user accounts and I run no servers. Booru Browser ships with no
    default server list. It only connects to the booru sites <em>you</em> choose to
    add, and it talks to them directly from your device. I do not host, proxy,
    cache on my behalf, or relay any of that traffic.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party sites and content</h2>
  <p>
    The images, tags, and other content you browse come from independent
    third-party services that I neither operate, control, nor endorse. Each site
    has its own terms of service, content, and rules, and your use of any site
    through the app is subject to that site’s terms. You are responsible for
    reviewing and complying with them, including any rules on API access, rate
    limits, and acceptable use.
  </p>
  <p>
    I make no guarantee that any particular site will be reachable, will keep
    working, or will return any particular content. Sites may change, restrict
    access, or shut down at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You agree not to use Booru Browser to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>access, store, or distribute content that is illegal where you live;</li>
    <li>violate the terms, rules, or technical limits of any site you connect to;</li>
    <li>infringe the rights of artists or other rights holders; or</li>
    <li>break any applicable law or regulation.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You are solely responsible for the servers you add, the searches you run, and
    the media you view, download, or share.
  </p>

  <h2>Mature content and age</h2>
  <p>
    Booru Browser is rated 17+. Mature content is hidden by default and stays
    locked behind an explicit age confirmation that you must enable yourself. By
    unlocking it, you confirm that you are of legal age to view such material where
    you live and that doing so is lawful there. The app is not directed to children.
  </p>

  <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    Booru Browser does not own, license, or claim any rights to the content served
    by third-party sites. All artwork and other media remain the property of their
    respective creators and rights holders. Downloading or sharing media does not
    grant you any rights to it, and you are responsible for using it lawfully.
  </p>

  <h2>No warranty</h2>
  <p>
    The app is provided “as is” and “as available”, without warranties of any kind,
    whether express or implied, including fitness for a particular purpose and
    non-infringement. I do not warrant that the app will be uninterrupted, secure,
    or error-free.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, I am not liable for any indirect,
    incidental, or consequential damages, or for any loss of data, arising from
    your use of the app or of any third-party site accessed through it. Because the
    app is free, your sole remedy if you are unhappy with it is to stop using it
    and uninstall it.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    These terms may change over time. Updates will be posted on this page with a
    revised “last updated” date, and your continued use of the app after a change
    means you accept the new terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms? Email
    <a href="mailto:chris@watzon.tech">chris@watzon.tech</a>.
  </p>
</BooruLegalLayout>
